Ethics and Anti-Corruption Commission CEO Twalib Mbarak has bid farewell to outgoing chairman Eliud Wabukala. Wabukala's term ended on Tuesday, January 17, 2023. The CEO lauded Wabukala for his contribution to the Commission, wishing him God's blessings in his future endeavours. "On behalf of the Commissioner, Executives Management and Staff of EACC. I thank the outgoing Chairperson for the focused and steady leadership that he provided to the Commission in the last six years," Twalib said. Wabukala was appointed to the position on January 18, 2017, via a gazette notice by retired President Uhuru Kenyatta. Twalib said he was "instrumental in shaping the strategic and policy direction of the Commission". The CEO added that under Wabukala's leadership, the integrity body realised significant milestones in the fight against corruption and promotion of ethics in the country. "EACC appreciates that Archbishop Wabukala leaves a stable, professional and reliable Anti-Corruption Agency that is committed to the effective discharge of its mandate to the people of Kenya," Twalib added.